the idea that true wisdom lies in recognizing that one knows nothing.
how the examined life is the only one worth living.
the paradox that virtue is knowledge, and thus, no one does evil willingly.
the belief that ignorance is the root of all evil, and knowledge leads to virtue.
the method of seeking truth through questioning and dialogue.
the understanding that no one errs or does wrong knowingly, as virtue is tied to knowledge.
the emphasis on self-examination and the constant pursuit of understanding my own beliefs.
the view that the goal of education is to draw out knowledge already present in the soul.
the use of irony, feigning ignorance to stimulate critical thinking in conversations.
the legacy of influencing Western philosophy by emphasizing ethics, logic, and the pursuit of truth.
